                                        How do I determine the quality of an opal?
                                    </button>
                                </h2>
                                <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingFive" data-bs-parent="#accordionPurchasing">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>Opal quality is determined by several factors:</p>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li><strong>Play-of-Color:</strong> The intensity, range, and pattern of colors displayed. Reds and blues are typically more valuable than greens and yellows.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Body Tone:</strong> The background color of the opal. Darker body tones (black or dark gray) generally command higher prices as they provide better contrast for the play-of-color.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Pattern:</strong> The arrangement of the color. Patterns like "harlequin" (mosaic-like squares of color) are rare and highly valued.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Brightness:</strong> How vividly the colors flash when the stone is moved.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Size and Shape:</strong> Larger opals with good color are rarer and more valuable.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Clarity:</strong> The absence of visible inclusions or flaws.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <p>At Ottawa Opal Shop, our experts can guide you through these factors to help you select the perfect opal for your preferences and budget.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
