                        <div class="accordion" id="accordionCare">
                            <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingEight">
                                    <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseEight" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseEight">
                                        How should I clean my opal jewelry?
                                    </button>
                                </h2>
                                <div id="collapseEight" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingEight" data-bs-parent="#accordionCare">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>To clean your opal jewelry safely:</p>
                                        <ol>
                                            <li>Use a soft, damp cloth to gently wipe the surface of the opal.</li>
                                            <li>For more thorough cleaning, use lukewarm water with a mild soap (like diluted dish soap).</li>
                                            <li>Gently clean with a soft cloth or a very soft brush (like a baby toothbrush).</li>
                                            <li>Rinse thoroughly with clean lukewarm water.</li>
                                            <li>Pat dry with a soft, lint-free cloth and allow to air dry completely before storing.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                        <p><strong>Important: Never use</strong> ultrasonic cleaners, steam cleaners, or harsh chemicals on opals. These can damage the stone's structure and affect its appearance.</p>
                                        <p>For professional cleaning, bring your opal jewelry to Ottawa Opal Shop, where our experts will clean it using safe, specialized methods.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="accordion-item mb-3">
                                <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingNine">
                                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseNine" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseNine">
                                        Can opals be worn every day?
                                    </button>
                                </h2>
                                <div id="collapseNine" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingNine" data-bs-parent="#accordionCare">
                                    <div class="accordion-body">
                                        <p>Opals can be worn regularly, but they require more care than harder gemstones like diamonds or sapphires. Here are some considerations for everyday wear:</p>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li><strong>Hardness:</strong> Opals rank 5.5-6.5 on the Mohs hardness scale, making them more susceptible to scratches than harder gemstones.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Settings:</strong> Protective settings like bezels or halos can help shield opals from impacts.</li>
                                            <li><strong>Activities:</strong> Remove opal jewelry before activities that might expose it to impacts, chemicals, or extreme temperatures.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <p>For everyday wear, consider:</p>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li>Opal earrings or pendants, which are less exposed to impacts than rings</li>
                                            <li>Triplet or doublet opals, which have added durability</li>
                                            <li>Boulder opals, which have natural ironstone backing for added strength</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <p>With proper care and awareness, many of our customers enjoy wearing their opal jewelry regularly for many years.</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
